# Testing Rules

**Note:** This rule provides specific testing guidance. For architectural testability requirements, see `nestjs-architecture.mdc` section 8.

## Test Coverage Requirements

- **Minimum coverage: 80%**
- **Required tests for:**
  - All services (unit tests) - must be testable without database (see `nestjs-architecture.mdc` section 8)
  - All controllers (e2e tests for critical endpoints)
  - Guards and interceptors
  - Complex business processes (request → proposal → deal flow)

## Test Structure

- `*.spec.ts` - Unit tests (next to the file)
- `*.e2e-spec.ts` - E2E tests (in `test/` directory or module)

## Testing Tools

- Use Jest and @nestjs/testing
- Mock dependencies in unit tests
- Use test database for e2e tests

## Unit Test Example

```typescript
import { Test } from '@nestjs/testing';
import { getModelToken } from '@nestjs/mongoose';
import { Model } from 'mongoose';
import { RequestsService } from './requests.service';
import { Request, RequestDocument } from '../../database/schemas/request.schema';

describe('RequestsService', () => {
  let service: RequestsService;
  let requestModel: Model<RequestDocument>;

  beforeEach(async () => {
    const module = await Test.createTestingModule({
      providers: [
        RequestsService,
        {
          provide: getModelToken(Request.name),
          useValue: {
            create: jest.fn(),
            find: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
              sort: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
                skip: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
                  limit: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
                    exec: jest.fn(),
                  }),
                }),
              }),
            }),
            findOne: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
              exec: jest.fn(),
            }),
            findById: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
              exec: jest.fn(),
            }),
            countDocuments: jest.fn().mockReturnValue({
              exec: jest.fn(),
            }),
          },
        },
        {
          provide: UsersService,
          useValue: {
            findOne: jest.fn(),
          },
        },
      ],
    }).compile();

    service = module.get<RequestsService>(RequestsService);
    requestModel = module.get<Model<RequestDocument>>(getModelToken(Request.name));
  });

  it('should create a request', async () => {
    // Arrange
    const dto = { title: 'Test', description: 'Test description', ... };
    const userId = '507f1f77bcf86cd799439011';
    const mockRequest = { _id: userId, ...dto, save: jest.fn() };
    
    jest.spyOn(requestModel, 'create').mockResolvedValue(mockRequest as any);
    
    // Act
    const result = await service.create(dto, userId);
    
    // Assert
    expect(requestModel.create).toHaveBeenCalled();
  });
});
```

## E2E Test Example

```typescript
describe('RequestsController (e2e)', () => {
  let app: INestApplication;
  let authToken: string;

  beforeAll(async () => {
    const moduleFixture = await Test.createTestingModule({
      imports: [AppModule],
    }).compile();

    app = moduleFixture.createNestApplication();
    await app.init();
    
    // Get token for tests
    const response = await request(app.getHttpServer())
      .post('/api/auth/login')
      .send({ email: 'test@example.com', password: 'password' });
    authToken = response.body.access_token;
  });

  it('/api/requests (POST) should create request', () => {
    return request(app.getHttpServer())
      .post('/api/requests')
      .set('Authorization', `Bearer ${authToken}`)
      .send({ title: 'Test', ... })
      .expect(201)
      .expect((res) => {
        expect(res.body).toHaveProperty('_id');
        expect(res.body.title).toBe('Test');
      });
  });
});
```

## Test Best Practices

- Use AAA pattern (Arrange, Act, Assert)
- Test one thing per test
- Use descriptive test names
- Mock external dependencies
- Test error cases
- Test edge cases
